Sentencas: The oxygen ion conductivity in the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) interconnection material LaCr0.85Mg0.15O3 has been studied with impedance spectroscopy in the temperature range of 650 to 1300 K using a solid state electrochemical cell comprising the semi-blocking electrodes Pt(02)/YSZ, and the interconnection material as the solid electrolyte.
Titulo: OXYGEN DIFFUSION IN THE SOFC INTERCONNECTION MATERIAL LACR(1-X)MGXO3

Sentencas: Oxygen ion vacancy diffusion in the interconnection material LaCr0.85Mg0.1503 is used to model the growth of gas-tight layers of this material by electrochemical vapor deposition (EVD) with the Wagner model for oxidation of metals.
Titulo: OXYGEN DIFFUSION IN THE SOFC INTERCONNECTION MATERIAL LACR(1-X)MGXO3
